  "title": "Calibration Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Key Responsibilities:</p><p>- Perform calibration for test/measurement instruments and other equipment onboard vessel, including:</p><ul><li>ODME, OWS, Fixed Gas Sampling /Detection System</li><li>Multi-gas Detector, Pressure/Temperature Gauge Calibration</li><li>UTI, Tank Gauging, Other Automation Services</li></ul><p>- Resolving onboard malfunctions, rectification of safety systems/ instruments, repairs and supply where applicable</p><p>- Produce Job Delivery Note upon job completion and issue calibration reports/certificates</p><p>- Proper preparation and execution of work assigned, prompt liaison with vessel agencies, and ensure performance are met at all times</p><p>- Assist our sales department with technical issues</p><p>- Support Service and Survey Department with other business service scopes<br /></p><p>Our customer service scope includes following:</p><ul><li>Lifeboat, rescue boat, davit and release gear inspection and servicing</li><li>Fire Fighting Equipment annual service and inspection</li><li>Liferaft annual inspection</li><li>Sample collection for Drug and Alcohol Test, Fresh water or drink water analysis</li><li>Cargo crane/Provision crane/Accommodation ladder/Pilot ladder load test</li><li>Flexible cargo hoses, piping lines pressure test</li><li>Magnetic compass adjustment, Deviation Card issuance</li><li>Gyro overhaul and services</li><li>Various ship flag/class survey, certification, inspections</li><li>Port Agency operation, Marine warranty survey, On/Off hire survey, Delivery and Re-delivery survey</li></ul><p>Company Website: <a href=\"http://www.starshipcare.sg/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><u>www.starshipcare.sg</u></a></p><p><br /></p><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>GCE “O”/ NITEC in relevant fields and above</li><li>Experience with calibration, trained on calibration of instruments and automated systems on board ships; similar role in a Marine or electrical background is a plus</li><li>Meticulous & methodical approach to service jobs and reports generation</li><li>Self-driven attitude to find solutions to problems</li><li>A team player and able to communicate effectively with colleagues and customers</li><li>Willingness to learn new skills and knowledge if no prior experience</li></ul><p>Interested candidates please send your CV (with photo) to our HR Head: Ms Lynda Lin, Email: <u>lynda.linli@gmail.com</u> (Regret only shortlisted will be invited for interview)</p>",
